            , were indicted, for that they <rs id="t17781021-38-off197" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17781021-38-off197" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17781021-38-off197" type="offenceSubcategory" value="highwayRobbery"></interp>
               in a certain field and open place, near the king's highway, in and upon 
                     
                        <persName id="t17781021-38-victim394" type="victimName">
                           Anne
                            Rawlinson
                        <interp inst="t17781021-38-victim394" type="surname" value="Rawlinson"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17781021-38-victim394" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17781021-38-victim394" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , <rs id="t17781021-38-viclabel198" type="occupation">spinster</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17781021-38-victim394 t17781021-38-viclabel198"></join>, feloniously did make an assault, putting her in corporal fear and danger of her life, and stealing from her person ten bobbins of silk, value 30 s. eight ounces of silk coloured warp, value 10 s. the property of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17781021-38-victim396" type="victimName">
                           Samuel
                            Cluen
                        <interp inst="t17781021-38-victim396" type="surname" value="Cluen"></interp>
